Reverse a Number
Example

Input: 1234
Output: 4321


ğŸ§  LOGIC 

Take last digit using % 10

Remove last digit using // 10

Add last digit to reversed number

CODE

def reverse_number(num):
    rev = 0
    while num > 0:
        digit = num % 10
        rev = rev * 10 + digit
        num = num // 10
    return rev


num = int(input("Enter number: "))
result = reverse_number(num)
print("Reversed number:", result)



ğŸ§  HOW FUNCTION WORKS

num â†’ input parameter

rev â†’ stores reversed value

Function returns reversed number

â± TIME & SPACE

Time Complexity: O(n)

Space Complexity: O(1)




VARIATION 1: Reverse a STRING (Using Slicing)

Python has slicing â†’ fastest & cleanest way.

CODE

def reverse_string(s):
    return s[::-1]


text = input("Enter string: ")
print("Reversed string:", reverse_string(text))

â± COMPLEXITY

Time: O(n)

Space: O(n)


VARIATION 2: Reverse a NEGATIVE NUMBER

ğŸ§  LOGIC

Store sign (- or +)

Reverse the absolute value

Attach sign back

CODE


def reverse_number_with_sign(num):
    sign = -1 if num < 0 else 1
    num = abs(num)

    rev = 0
    while num > 0:
        rev = rev * 10 + num % 10
        num //= 10

    return sign * rev


num = int(input("Enter number: "))
print("Reversed number:", reverse_number_with_sign(num))


ğŸ” EXAMPLE

Input: -123
Output: -321


ğŸš« VARIATION 3: Reverse a Number WITHOUT USING LOOP


ğŸ§  LOGIC

Convert number â†’ string â†’ reverse â†’ convert back

CODE


def reverse_without_loop(num):
    sign = -1 if num < 0 else 1
    num = abs(num)
    return sign * int(str(num)[::-1])


num = int(input("Enter number: "))
print("Reversed number:", reverse_without_loop(num))



VARIATION 4: Reverse a Number USING RECURSION



ğŸ§  LOGIC

Last digit goes first

Reduce number recursively

CODE

def reverse_recursive(num, rev=0):
    if num == 0:
        return rev
    return reverse_recursive(num // 10, rev * 10 + num % 10)


num = int(input("Enter number: "))
print("Reversed number:", reverse_recursive(abs(num)))

ğŸ” EXAMPLE

Input: 123
Output: 321





